<section class="sub-section sub-section-classes">

<h1 class="docs-header">Form Structure</h1>

<p>Along with all standard form elements, BaseWeb provides you with <code>.form-group</code>, <code>.input-group</code> and <code>.action-group</code> classes to use for structuring a form layout.</p>

<pre class="language-markup"><code>
&lt;form&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Example Label&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;input-group&quot;&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Example Label&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;input-group inline-group&quot;&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;action-group&quot;&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
</code></pre>

<div class="demo">
  <form>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Example Label</label>
      <div class="input-group">
        <input class="input" type="text" placeholder="Example text input..." required>
        <select class="input">
          <option>Option 1</option>
          <option>Option 2</option>
          <option>Option 3</option>
        </select>
        <textarea class="input" rows="4" placeholder="Example textarea..."></textarea>
      </div>
      
      <label>Example Label</label>
      <div class="input-group inline-group">
        <label class="choice"><input type="checkbox"> Choice checkbox</label>
        <label class="choice"><input type="radio"> Choice radio</label>
      </div>
    </div>
      
    <div class="action-group">
      <button class="btn btn-primary">Button</button>
      <button class="btn btn-default">Button</button>
    </div>
      
  </form>
</div>

<ul class="docs-list">

  <li>
    <h2 class="docs-header">.form-group</h2>
    <p>Form groups are the first structure element used in a BaseWeb forms. It applies our vertical spacing and a hook for adding modifier classes and custom styles.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2 class="docs-header">.input-group</h2>
    <p>Input groups are used to wrap groups of related input elements. It, like form groups, applies vertical spacing and another hook for adding modifier classes.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;input-group&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2 class="docs-header">.action-group</h2>
    <p>Action groups are used to wrap form submission, resets and other form actions. It's also a way to apply custom styles and modifiers as a form footer.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;action-group&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2 class="docs-header">.inline-group</h2>
    <p>You can create inline forms by adding the class <code>.inline-group</code> to form structure elements. If applied to a <code>.form-group</code> element, it also makes children <code>.form-group</code> and <code>.input-group</code> elements inline as well.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>
&lt;form&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group inline-group&quot;&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
    </code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <form>
        <div class="form-group inline-group">
          <input type="text" class="input" placeholder="Username" required>
          <input type="password" class="input" placeholder="Password" required>
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Sign In</button>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2 class="docs-header">Form Grids</h2>
    <p>For more complex form layouts, you also have BaseWeb's default grid system to create rows and columns. This is done using the <code>.row</code> <code>.col</code> and <code>.col-#</code> classes where <code>#</code> represents the number of columns to span.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>
&lt;form&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Grid Example&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col col-4&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col col-4&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col col-4&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
    </code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <form>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Grid Example</label>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col col-4">
              <input class="input" type="text" placeholder="Example">
            </div>
            <div class="col col-4">
              <select class="input">
                <option>Option 1</option>
                <option>Option 2</option>
                <option>Option 3</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="col col-4">
              <label class="choice"><input type="checkbox" checked> Choice</label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div><!-- .demo -->
  </li>

</ul>

</section>

